fields.title: Karimeen large
fields.short_description: It contains low fat, high protein, rich in omega 3 fatty acids.
fields.description: Also Known as the Pearl Spot, Easily one of our most sought after fish & the unofficial crown prince of Kerala fish that is equally popular all through India. It is a low-fat, high-protein food, rich in omega 3 fatty acids, which keep our heart and brain healthy.

fields.title: Poomeen large
fields.description: Apart from their mild flavor, milkfish is a good source of nutrients, vitamins and minerals. Consuming 85 gram of milkfish offers 2.78 µg of Vitamin B-12, 22.37 g of Protein, 7.018 mg of Vitamin B3, 0.415 mg of Vitamin B6, 177 mg of Phosphorus, 13.8 µg of Selenium, 7.34 g of Total Fat and 0.735 mg of Vitamin B5.

fields.title: Thirutha large
fields.short_description: The Thirutha as its known in the Southern Coasts is an amazing fish
fields.description: The Thirutha as its known in the Southern Coasts is an amazing fish that is generally found in both the fresh water and also in the slightly salty waters in the estuaries. This one is a real killer when it comes to the taste and is very sought after for delicious fish curries and fries.

fields.title: Kalanji large
fields.short_description: Also called the Asian Sea Bass
fields.description: The barramundi or Asian sea bass (Lates calcarifer) is a species of catadromous fish in family Latidae of order Perciformes

fields.title: Neymeen/Seer fish
fields.short_description: Seer fish is a delicacy in South India
fields.description: It is known as the king of fishes.It is a smell less fish.It is found in around the Indian Ocean and adjoining seas.

fields.title: Prawns/Chemmeen large
fields.short_description: Tasty fish which is considered a delicacy
fields.description: Prawns contain vitamins and minerals like calcium, phosphorous, potassium, vitamin A, vitamin E, etc. They are packed with significant amounts of vitamin B12, B6 and niacin. They are also a rich source of iron that helps in boosting the production of red blood cells.

fields.title: Mahi mahi / Pulli motha cleaned
fields.description: Mahi-mahi are swift and acrobatic game fish with striking colours.generaly used for making boneless fish fillets

fields.title: Yellow fin tuna / Kera Cleaned
fields.short_description: The high levels of omega-3 fatty acids in tuna fish may help to reduce the level of omega-6 fatty acids and LDL cholesterol that can accumulate inside the arteries of the heart
fields.description: The yellowfin tuna is a species of tuna found in pelagic waters of tropical and subtropical oceans worldwide.The yellowfin tuna is among the larger tuna species, reaching weights over 180 kg (400 lb)

fields.title: Vatta / Trevally Cleaned
fields.short_description: High in nutrients: Fatty fish is high in important nutrients such as Vitamin D and protein
fields.description: The Malabar trevally (Carangoides malabaricus), also known as the Malabar jack, Malabar kingfish or nakedshield kingfish, is a species of large inshore marine fish of the jack family, Carangidae.

fields.title: Butter fish / Punnarameen Cleaned
fields.short_description: Butterfish is also a source of iron and magnesium, vitamins B3 (niacin), B12 and D, phosphorus and selenium
fields.description: Minimal bones.Fish of this species are usually deep-bodied, flattened sideways, and somewhat circular or rounded, with blunt noses and small mouths with weak teeth. Some other characteristics of this fish are the absence of ventral fins, one long, continuous dorsal fin, long pectoral fins, and tiny, cycloid scales.

fields.title: Kadal kalanji / Sea bass Cleaned
fields.short_description: Kadal kalanji is packed with omega-3 fatty acids, healthy fats, protein, vitamin D, vitamin A, sodium and potassium
fields.description: his species has an elongated body form with a large, slightly oblique mouth and an upper jaw extending behind the eye
